verses.text:
“I have loved you,” says the LORD.
Yet you say, “How have you loved us?”
“Wasn’t Esau Jacob’s brother?” says the LORD, “Yet I loved Jacob;

You say also, ‘Behold, what a weariness it is!’ And you have sniffed at it”, says the LORD of Armies;
“and you have brought that which was taken by violence, the lame, and the sick; thus you bring the offering.
Should I accept this at your hand?” says the LORD.
